(71, 1, '2024-03-28 12:31:06', '2024-03-28 12:31:06', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The GTA 6 trailer is here and it has confirmed the Grand Theft Auto 6 location, characters, and release window</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:post-featured-image /-->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>GTA 6 is coming in 2025, with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.gamesradar.com/uk/tag/rockstar-games/\">Rockstar Games</a>&nbsp;taking us back to the sun-soaked streets of Vice City. The reveal of the first official&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.gamesradar.com/gta-6-trailer-1/\">GTA 6 trailer</a>&nbsp;gave us a pretty spectacular look at Leonida, hinting towards some of the wild sights and sounds that the state will have to offer us.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you\'re looking for more insight into the trailer, you\'ll want to check out our in-depth&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.gamesradar.com/gta-6-trailer-1-breakdown-things-you-missed/\">GTA 6 trailer breakdown</a>. In it, we try to unpick some story details about Lucia â€“ the protagonist leading Grand Theft Auto 6 â€“ as well as get a better sense of the sort of scale which Rockstar is striving for. It\'s all exceptionally impressive, and there\'s plenty to dig into. So with that in mind, you\'ll want to keep on reading to find everything you need to know about GTA 6 ahead of its release next year.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'GTA 6: Everything we know so far', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'gta-6-everything-we-know-so-far', '', '', '2024-03-28 12:31:11', '2024-03-28 12:31:11', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=71', 0, 'post', '', 0),
